[
  {
    "text": "Who could have predicted\nthat one of the Internet's",
    "start": 0.625,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "most elaborate\nfandom communities",
    "start": 2.293,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "would begin with a single post",
    "start": 4.045,
    "duration": 1.627
  },
  {
    "text": "on June 22nd, 2007?",
    "start": 5.755,
    "duration": 1.919
  },
  {
    "text": "Uploaded on 4chan's\nParanormal X board,",
    "start": 7.757,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "the statute read like\na government case file,",
    "start": 10.719,
    "duration": 2.293
  },
  {
    "text": "and opened with\na provocative warning:",
    "start": 13.096,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Special containment procedures,",
    "start": 14.889,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Item SCP-173 is to be\nkept in a locked container",
    "start": 17.058,
    "duration": 3.087
  },
  {
    "text": "at all times.\"",
    "start": 20.228,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "The entry describes an\nanimate and malevolent figure,",
    "start": 21.813,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "made of concrete and rebar,",
    "start": 24.232,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "with indications it had been\nspray-painted at one time.",
    "start": 25.859,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "It is housed in a large room\nwith unbarred windows.",
    "start": 29.07,
    "duration": 2.544
  },
  {
    "text": "When alone,\nsounds of stone scraping",
    "start": 31.698,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "can be heard.",
    "start": 33.616,
    "duration": 1.085
  },
  {
    "text": "It will fill its container",
    "start": 34.784,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "with a mixture of\nreddish brown material,",
    "start": 36.035,
    "duration": 2.128
  },
  {
    "text": "believed to be a combination\nof feces and blood,",
    "start": 38.246,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "but the scariest part,",
    "start": 41.124,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "blink and it will kill you.",
    "start": 42.584,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "Although the post would be\ndeleted a few days later,",
    "start": 44.252,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "the strange entry\nsparked the imagination",
    "start": 46.629,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "of the X community,",
    "start": 49.132,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "suggesting the existence",
    "start": 50.55,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "of a secret government\norganization",
    "start": 51.885,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "dedicated to collecting",
    "start": 53.762,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "and containing\npreternatural entities.",
    "start": 54.971,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "Yeah, that's the perfect\nstart for worldbuilding.",
    "start": 57.223,
    "duration": 3.045
  },
  {
    "text": "[spirited music]",
    "start": 60.351,
    "duration": 1.419
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm Dr. Emily Zarka,",
    "start": 61.853,
    "duration": 1.627
  },
  {
    "text": "and this is \"Monstrum.\"",
    "start": 63.563,
    "duration": 2.377
  },
  {
    "text": "This strange entry in 2007",
    "start": 66.024,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "was the genesis of\nwhat we now know",
    "start": 68.276,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "as the SCP Foundation,",
    "start": 70.153,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "a spooky, fictional universe",
    "start": 71.988,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "centered around a Wiki that\nhosts thousands of posts,",
    "start": 74.032,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "from contributors\nacross the globe",
    "start": 76.91,
    "duration": 2.043
  },
  {
    "text": "who contribute to its lore.",
    "start": 79.037,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "SCP Foundation is\ncrowdsourced folklore",
    "start": 80.622,
    "duration": 2.627
  },
  {
    "text": "at some of its finest.",
    "start": 83.333,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "And it takes\ncollaborative fiction",
    "start": 84.793,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "to a whole new dimension.",
    "start": 86.544,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "While it's tempting\nto dismiss the SCP",
    "start": 88.338,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "as some crazy\nconspiracy website,",
    "start": 90.423,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "the administrators clearly\nand frequently acknowledge",
    "start": 92.509,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "that the Foundation\nis essentially an art",
    "start": 95.303,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "and creative writing experiment.",
    "start": 97.514,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "In their words, \"The Foundation,",
    "start": 99.098,
    "duration": 1.919
  },
  {
    "text": "\"its anomalies,\nand everything else",
    "start": 101.1,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "that's been written\nabout is fictional.\"",
    "start": 102.977,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "But that doesn't\nmake it any less fun.",
    "start": 104.938,
    "duration": 2.252
  },
  {
    "text": "Quite the opposite.",
    "start": 107.273,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "According to the lore,",
    "start": 108.483,
    "duration": 0.917
  },
  {
    "text": "the SCP Foundation",
    "start": 109.484,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "is a nebulous international\ngroup of individuals,",
    "start": 111.027,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "who identify, capture,\nand contain supernatural",
    "start": 113.822,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "and preternatural anomalies,",
    "start": 116.741,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "with the full support of every\nmajor national government.",
    "start": 118.91,
    "duration": 3.086
  },
  {
    "text": "Kind of like the\n\"Men in Black\" and \"Area 51\"",
    "start": 122.08,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "meets \"The X-Files.\"",
    "start": 124.332,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "Their official slogan--",
    "start": 125.75,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "\"We secure, we contain,\nwe protect.\"",
    "start": 127.043,
    "duration": 2.503
  },
  {
    "text": "Objects like the\nmalevolent IKEA store,",
    "start": 129.629,
    "duration": 2.377
  },
  {
    "text": "Shy Guy, The Old Man,",
    "start": 132.09,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "or the endless staircase,",
    "start": 133.591,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "are iconic\nto the Foundation's lore.",
    "start": 135.468,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "If you've been on any horror\ncorner of the internet,",
    "start": 137.554,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "you've probably felt\nthe lingering presence",
    "start": 139.764,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "of the SCP in games,",
    "start": 141.683,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "short films,\nfiction, and fan art.",
    "start": 143.685,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "Part of that is because\ninstead of being beholden",
    "start": 145.937,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "to copyright and ownership,",
    "start": 148.147,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "which can restrict\na story's ability to adapt,",
    "start": 149.899,
    "duration": 2.461
  },
  {
    "text": "each SCP universe entry is\npart of a collective tradition",
    "start": 152.443,
    "duration": 3.587
  },
  {
    "text": "that is ever-evolving.",
    "start": 156.114,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "And the lore spreads quickly.",
    "start": 157.574,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "While many people,",
    "start": 159.325,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "rightfully, tend to hold\nolder legends and folklore",
    "start": 161.077,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "in reverence for their\nhistorical significance",
    "start": 162.37,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "and insights into\nevolving communities,",
    "start": 165.373,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "the SCP Foundation\noffers something more,",
    "start": 166.875,
    "duration": 3.586
  },
  {
    "text": "a unique perspective into\nhow stories and monsters",
    "start": 170.545,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "evolve in real time.",
    "start": 173.256,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "The community is\nopen to any member",
    "start": 175.133,
    "duration": 1.626
  },
  {
    "text": "who would like to post.",
    "start": 176.843,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "Most entries are told\nthrough case files,",
    "start": 178.136,
    "duration": 2.502
  },
  {
    "text": "fiction, written in\na pseudoscientific report style,",
    "start": 180.722,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "that details the special\ncontainment procedures",
    "start": 183.683,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "of the anomaly,",
    "start": 186.06,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "followed by a detailed\ndescription of the event,",
    "start": 187.645,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "object, or entity,",
    "start": 189.314,
    "duration": 1.167
  },
  {
    "text": "and how it was contained.",
    "start": 190.565,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "Each of these entries",
    "start": 191.983,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "is given a three- or\nfour-digit SCP number",
    "start": 193.318,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "and brief title.",
    "start": 195.361,
    "duration": 0.96
  },
  {
    "text": "Some images may be included,",
    "start": 196.404,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as addendums",
    "start": 197.78,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "that contribute to\nthe understanding",
    "start": 199.157,
    "duration": 1.334
  },
  {
    "text": "of the artifact,",
    "start": 200.575,
    "duration": 1.084
  },
  {
    "text": "and how it is\naffecting or responding",
    "start": 201.743,
    "duration": 1.626
  },
  {
    "text": "to its surroundings.",
    "start": 203.453,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "In more recent years,",
    "start": 204.954,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "creative authors have even\nproduced interactive pages",
    "start": 206.623,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "that evoke all sorts of\nreal-world technologies.",
    "start": 208.666,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "Unlike many other fictional\nsupernatural organizations,",
    "start": 211.878,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "the SCP Foundation is\nincredibly bureaucratic,",
    "start": 213.88,
    "duration": 4.212
  },
  {
    "text": "which contributes to\na successful worldbuilding.",
    "start": 218.176,
    "duration": 2.377
  },
  {
    "text": "Bureaucracy is\nsomething many of us",
    "start": 220.637,
    "duration": 1.876
  },
  {
    "text": "are all well too familiar with.",
    "start": 222.597,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "And utilizing this common\ncultural understanding",
    "start": 224.682,
    "duration": 2.795
  },
  {
    "text": "allows for\na more-ready entry point",
    "start": 227.56,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "into the Foundation's world.",
    "start": 229.479,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "Supporting this connection\nis SCP's rhetorical style,",
    "start": 231.147,
    "duration": 3.337
  },
  {
    "text": "which mimics classified\ngovernment texts,",
    "start": 234.567,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "especially redacted documents.",
    "start": 236.694,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "Common themes can be found",
    "start": 238.863,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "throughout the\nFoundation's many entries.",
    "start": 240.323,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "Fear or reticence of technology,",
    "start": 242.45,
    "duration": 2.211
  },
  {
    "text": "viral communication,",
    "start": 244.744,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "scientific or governmental\nfailure to control danger,",
    "start": 246.412,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "definitions of sentience,",
    "start": 249.248,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "doppelganger and\nhybrid-being anxiety,",
    "start": 250.667,
    "duration": 2.335
  },
  {
    "text": "but that's just\nthe tip of the iceberg.",
    "start": 253.086,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "There's Josie, the half cat,",
    "start": 255.296,
    "duration": 1.961
  },
  {
    "text": "hidden exoplanets\nwith alien life forms,",
    "start": 257.34,
    "duration": 2.461
  },
  {
    "text": "a coffee vending machine",
    "start": 259.884,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "that can produce any\nliquid on demand,",
    "start": 261.177,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "a strangely helpful,\nstar-shaped nightlight,",
    "start": 263.012,
    "duration": 2.252
  },
  {
    "text": "a pool of what\nappears to be blood",
    "start": 265.348,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "from which extremely\nhostile entities",
    "start": 266.975,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "occasionally exit,",
    "start": 268.977,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "and the remains of\na murdered woman",
    "start": 270.311,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "that cause horrific\ndeaths and disappearances.",
    "start": 271.98,
    "duration": 2.585
  },
  {
    "text": "These objects,",
    "start": 274.649,
    "duration": 0.959
  },
  {
    "text": "along with thousands of others,",
    "start": 275.692,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "are labeled as one\nof 11 object classes.",
    "start": 277.694,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "Separated into common\nprimary classes",
    "start": 279.779,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "and non-standard object classes,",
    "start": 282.699,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "the categories range from safe,",
    "start": 284.909,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "meaning threatening,",
    "start": 286.828,
    "duration": 0.876
  },
  {
    "text": "but easily and safely contained",
    "start": 287.787,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "with minimal\nFoundational effort,",
    "start": 289.288,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "to anomalies that\nrequire massive effort",
    "start": 291.04,
    "duration": 2.211
  },
  {
    "text": "to be dealt with.",
    "start": 293.334,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "Usually associated with\na world-ending threat.",
    "start": 294.752,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "Objects in this class\ncannot be contained,",
    "start": 296.713,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "are indestructible,",
    "start": 299.215,
    "duration": 1.043
  },
  {
    "text": "and/or are expected to escape.",
    "start": 300.341,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "An object's class is determined",
    "start": 302.552,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "by the informal Locked Box Test.",
    "start": 304.345,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "According to Foundation lore,",
    "start": 307.265,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "most autonomous, alive,\nand/or sapien objects,",
    "start": 308.808,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "are, at least, Euclid-class,",
    "start": 311.644,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "meaning, you can\nlock it in a box,",
    "start": 313.896,
    "duration": 1.836
  },
  {
    "text": "but you're not sure\nwhat will happen.",
    "start": 315.815,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "The authors of these texts\nare tapping into attention",
    "start": 317.692,
    "duration": 2.544
  },
  {
    "text": "that exists across\nmany populations,",
    "start": 320.319,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "fear that our governments",
    "start": 322.739,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "may not be telling\nus the whole story,",
    "start": 324.073,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "and raise questions about if\nsuch information withholding",
    "start": 325.908,
    "duration": 3.337
  },
  {
    "text": "is productive or destructive.",
    "start": 329.328,
    "duration": 2.461
  },
  {
    "text": "And that's exactly\nwhat the original,",
    "start": 331.873,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "2007 4chan post provided,",
    "start": 333.124,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "a story that taps\ninto people's fears",
    "start": 336.085,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "and mistrust of the government,",
    "start": 337.67,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as their ability to\ncontain their secrets safely.",
    "start": 339.464,
    "duration": 3.086
  },
  {
    "text": "We might not have\nknown the source",
    "start": 342.633,
    "duration": 1.419
  },
  {
    "text": "of the original SCP-173",
    "start": 344.135,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "if it weren't for\nthe online sleuth",
    "start": 346.554,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "dasMaymay, who brought\nthe original entry",
    "start": 348.181,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "back to the Internet's awareness",
    "start": 350.475,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "after some archive\nsearching in 2018.",
    "start": 352.143,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "Fans of Dr. Who",
    "start": 354.854,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "may note the similarities\nbetween the weeping angels",
    "start": 356.397,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "and SCP-173.",
    "start": 358.441,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "While this connection\nhas not been confirmed,",
    "start": 360.318,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "for Dr. Who fans,",
    "start": 362.528,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "this narrative serves\nas an extension",
    "start": 363.946,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "of something that already\nexists in popular culture,",
    "start": 365.74,
    "duration": 2.961
  },
  {
    "text": "but brings it\ninto a larger organization,",
    "start": 368.785,
    "duration": 2.085
  },
  {
    "text": "and hints at\nits real-world existence",
    "start": 370.953,
    "duration": 2.128
  },
  {
    "text": "by using familiar bureaucratic\nlanguage and style.",
    "start": 373.164,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "Administrators of\nthe Wiki now note",
    "start": 376.125,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "that SCP-173 is\nuniquely inspiring,",
    "start": 377.96,
    "duration": 3.254
  },
  {
    "text": "because it relies on\nthe fear that emerges",
    "start": 381.297,
    "duration": 2.085
  },
  {
    "text": "from wonder and possibility,",
    "start": 383.466,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "rather than a jump scare.",
    "start": 385.343,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "The original five large\nthreads that emerged",
    "start": 386.928,
    "duration": 2.377
  },
  {
    "text": "on 4chans X Forum\nin January, 2008,",
    "start": 389.388,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "dedicated to expanding\nthe SCP universe,",
    "start": 392.225,
    "duration": 2.627
  },
  {
    "text": "became known as the SCP Series.",
    "start": 394.936,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "The popularity of the work\nwas deemed important enough,",
    "start": 397.814,
    "duration": 2.335
  },
  {
    "text": "or cool enough,",
    "start": 400.233,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "that, on January 19th,\nsomeone made a Wiki",
    "start": 401.609,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "for all of the SCP-themed posts",
    "start": 403.736,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "that began popping up,",
    "start": 405.947,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "so that the content wouldn't\nbe lost to the ether.",
    "start": 407.573,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "Originally housed on\nthe EditThis Wiki farm,",
    "start": 410.409,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "anyone at any time\ncould edit the stories.",
    "start": 412.37,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "Discussion boards\nexisted for every page.",
    "start": 414.872,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "User, FritzWillie, saw that\nstories were being deleted",
    "start": 417.583,
    "duration": 2.253
  },
  {
    "text": "by the EditThis hosting network,",
    "start": 419.919,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "and moved the entirety of\nthe community's content",
    "start": 421.671,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "to a WikiDot,",
    "start": 424.59,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "which went live on\nJuly 25th, 2008.",
    "start": 425.883,
    "duration": 2.878
  },
  {
    "text": "This move introduced a page\nrating and comment system,",
    "start": 428.845,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "and moderators were introduced.",
    "start": 431.639,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "Everything was\nstill open source.",
    "start": 432.89,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "Any user could edit\nany post they wanted.",
    "start": 435.685,
    "duration": 2.627
  },
  {
    "text": "Until someone\ncreated spam threads",
    "start": 438.396,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "and started deleting\nstuff en masse.",
    "start": 440.189,
    "duration": 2.461
  },
  {
    "text": "Longtime users decided to\nremove anonymous edits,",
    "start": 442.733,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "and an administration\nteam emerged.",
    "start": 445.528,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "Eventually, to keep the spirit\nof the original SCP Series,",
    "start": 448.03,
    "duration": 3.129
  },
  {
    "text": "and ensure that the quality\nof content was maintained,",
    "start": 451.242,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "banning was enacted,",
    "start": 453.953,
    "duration": 1.21
  },
  {
    "text": "and more strict editing\npolicies put in place.",
    "start": 455.246,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "The community's dedication",
    "start": 457.54,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "to preserving the\nearly work of the genre",
    "start": 458.833,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "is not just something\nI appreciate;",
    "start": 460.042,
    "duration": 2.795
  },
  {
    "text": "it's absolutely crucial",
    "start": 462.92,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "to establishing any\nkind of standard",
    "start": 464.463,
    "duration": 1.961
  },
  {
    "text": "or canon for the genre.",
    "start": 466.507,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "I also think it shows\na really lovely dedication",
    "start": 468.342,
    "duration": 2.253
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Foundation's community.",
    "start": 470.678,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "The internet can often feel\nlike a lawless country,",
    "start": 472.555,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "but when it comes to\nthe SCP Foundation,",
    "start": 474.849,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "rules help preserve\nits integrity.",
    "start": 476.1,
    "duration": 2.628
  },
  {
    "text": "Because most of the\ncontent posted to the site",
    "start": 478.811,
    "duration": 2.086
  },
  {
    "text": "is allowed to be adapted,",
    "start": 480.98,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "recreated, or reused,",
    "start": 482.231,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "The Foundation's universe\nhas served as inspiration",
    "start": 484.15,
    "duration": 2.335
  },
  {
    "text": "for many other creative works.",
    "start": 486.569,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "There was a theater\ncontribution to the lore,",
    "start": 488.946,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "Welcome to the Ethics Committee,",
    "start": 490.74,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "performed in Dublin,",
    "start": 491.991,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "a concert in Glasgow,",
    "start": 493.242,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "various video games,",
    "start": 494.827,
    "duration": 1.377
  },
  {
    "text": "a serialized novel in Japan,",
    "start": 496.287,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "and a graphic novel.",
    "start": 497.705,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "While these elements testify\nto the widespread popularity",
    "start": 499.373,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "of the SCP Foundation universe,",
    "start": 501.751,
    "duration": 2.335
  },
  {
    "text": "its primary presence\nonline seems most important",
    "start": 504.17,
    "duration": 3.045
  },
  {
    "text": "to its worldbuilding.",
    "start": 507.298,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "The internet is\ninherently liminal,",
    "start": 508.674,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "which can make sharing stories",
    "start": 510.468,
    "duration": 1.084
  },
  {
    "text": "that seem real, but aren't,",
    "start": 511.636,
    "duration": 1.167
  },
  {
    "text": "more efficient.",
    "start": 512.887,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "The SCP's case-file approach,",
    "start": 514.18,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "and vaguely scientific rhetoric,",
    "start": 515.973,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "blurs the boundaries\nbetween the real",
    "start": 517.808,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "and the not-real,",
    "start": 519.769,
    "duration": 1.042
  },
  {
    "text": "in a space many people approach",
    "start": 520.895,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "as both permanent and nebulous.",
    "start": 522.521,
    "duration": 2.128
  },
  {
    "text": "Virtual reality is a ready space",
    "start": 524.732,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "for imagined realities.",
    "start": 526.776,
    "duration": 2.21
  },
  {
    "text": "But that's not to say there\naren't educational lessons",
    "start": 529.07,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "in the archives of the SCP,",
    "start": 531.03,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "or that they don't\ncontribute to social policing",
    "start": 532.823,
    "duration": 1.961
  },
  {
    "text": "and understandings\nof deviant behavior.",
    "start": 534.867,
    "duration": 2.211
  },
  {
    "text": "Like all explorations\ninto monsters and fear,",
    "start": 537.161,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "it's about pushing\nthe boundaries",
    "start": 539.58,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "of what scares or unsettles us,",
    "start": 541.123,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "and why.",
    "start": 543.0,
    "duration": 1.377
  },
  {
    "text": "These elements are even debated",
    "start": 544.46,
    "duration": 1.71
  },
  {
    "text": "in the Foundation's\ndiscussion boards.",
    "start": 546.254,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "Take something like SCP-1919,",
    "start": 548.464,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "for instance,",
    "start": 550.591,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "a Euclid-class object that\nrequires a containment perimeter",
    "start": 552.134,
    "duration": 2.378
  },
  {
    "text": "with a two-kilometer radius,",
    "start": 554.595,
    "duration": 1.919
  },
  {
    "text": "since it presents as a decaying,",
    "start": 556.597,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "early 20th-century hotel\nand converted mansion.",
    "start": 558.182,
    "duration": 3.295
  },
  {
    "text": "If a human enters the building,",
    "start": 561.56,
    "duration": 1.836
  },
  {
    "text": "it produces multiple humanoid\nreplicas of that person,",
    "start": 563.479,
    "duration": 3.587
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as anything\nthey are carrying.",
    "start": 567.149,
    "duration": 2.503
  },
  {
    "text": "For this reason,",
    "start": 569.735,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "personnel cannot carry\nbody armor or weapons.",
    "start": 571.112,
    "duration": 2.419
  },
  {
    "text": "These Replicants are\nnot perfect bones.",
    "start": 573.614,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "They have physical\nabnormalities,",
    "start": 575.992,
    "duration": 1.167
  },
  {
    "text": "like sealed nostrils,",
    "start": 577.243,
    "duration": 0.959
  },
  {
    "text": "or improper proportions",
    "start": 578.286,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "that mark them as Replicants.",
    "start": 579.745,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "There are enough of these\nthat after Expedition Two,",
    "start": 581.872,
    "duration": 2.294
  },
  {
    "text": "when aggressive Replicants",
    "start": 584.25,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "referred to as\nSCP-19191 emerged.",
    "start": 585.501,
    "duration": 3.754
  },
  {
    "text": "There are apparently\nenough of these",
    "start": 589.338,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "that they function as\na coordinated ant colony,",
    "start": 590.715,
    "duration": 2.794
  },
  {
    "text": "made and controlled by\na singular female being.",
    "start": 593.592,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "Any entry is currently halted",
    "start": 596.596,
    "duration": 1.584
  },
  {
    "text": "until all manifestations\ncan be expected",
    "start": 598.264,
    "duration": 2.669
  },
  {
    "text": "to have starved to death.",
    "start": 601.017,
    "duration": 1.584
  },
  {
    "text": "Okay, there's a lot\nto unpack there,",
    "start": 602.685,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "but the hive zombie mentality,",
    "start": 604.812,
    "duration": 1.627
  },
  {
    "text": "aggressive mob violence,",
    "start": 606.522,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "and mysterious Replicant leader",
    "start": 607.857,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "called to mind many\nreal-world fears",
    "start": 609.608,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "of overpopulation,",
    "start": 611.736,
    "duration": 1.376
  },
  {
    "text": "destructive groupthink,",
    "start": 613.195,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "and even urban decay,",
    "start": 614.28,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "giving the buildings\ndecrepit appearance.",
    "start": 615.906,
    "duration": 2.503
  },
  {
    "text": "But those are just\nmy interpretations.",
    "start": 618.492,
    "duration": 2.67
  },
  {
    "text": "I think that's where\na lot of the real genius",
    "start": 621.245,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "comes from\nin the SCP Foundation.",
    "start": 623.205,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "Just enough\ninformation is given,",
    "start": 625.333,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "and given impassively enough,",
    "start": 627.084,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "that your mind goes crazy,",
    "start": 629.045,
    "duration": 1.459
  },
  {
    "text": "trying to fill in the blanks.",
    "start": 630.588,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "There seem to be no completed\nstories or case files,",
    "start": 632.506,
    "duration": 2.92
  },
  {
    "text": "which means infinite exploration",
    "start": 635.509,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "of what scares us is possible.",
    "start": 637.345,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "In my opinion,",
    "start": 639.388,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "in some ways, there's\neven greater potential",
    "start": 640.765,
    "duration": 1.626
  },
  {
    "text": "for legend growth,",
    "start": 642.475,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "and significance through\nonline global communities,",
    "start": 644.101,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "like the SCP Foundation.",
    "start": 645.77,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "They allow stories\nto cultivate quickly",
    "start": 647.646,
    "duration": 1.544
  },
  {
    "text": "and in nuanced ways",
    "start": 649.273,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "that translate\ntheir relatability",
    "start": 650.608,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "across disparate communities.",
    "start": 652.151,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "Telling these stories\nis performative,",
    "start": 653.402,
    "duration": 2.503
  },
  {
    "text": "a form of communication\nthat allows for others",
    "start": 655.988,
    "duration": 2.044
  },
  {
    "text": "to offer their own alterations",
    "start": 658.115,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "to the text in real-time.",
    "start": 659.7,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "The appreciation for recreating",
    "start": 661.577,
    "duration": 1.794
  },
  {
    "text": "and retelling the stories,",
    "start": 663.454,
    "duration": 1.126
  },
  {
    "text": "without fear of\ncopyright infringement,",
    "start": 664.663,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "is an interpretive freedom\nthat's actually really powerful.",
    "start": 667.083,
    "duration": 3.169
  },
  {
    "text": "It hearkens back to more\ntraditional lore evolution,",
    "start": 670.336,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "just without geographic\nor language boundaries.",
    "start": 673.13,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "While, \"We secure,\nwe contain, we protect\"",
    "start": 675.966,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "is their official slogan,",
    "start": 678.219,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "dare I add, \"We teach\"?",
    "start": 679.553,
    "duration": 2.503
  },
  {
    "text": "While not an educational tool\nby design,",
    "start": 682.139,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "the collaborative format",
    "start": 684.35,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "can advance participants'\nmultimedia communication skills.",
    "start": 685.976,
    "duration": 3.212
  },
  {
    "text": "The creative guidelines,",
    "start": 689.271,
    "duration": 0.918
  },
  {
    "text": "open authorship,",
    "start": 690.272,
    "duration": 0.96
  },
  {
    "text": "an informal peer review process",
    "start": 691.315,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "covers many\nof the fundamental components",
    "start": 693.234,
    "duration": 1.793
  },
  {
    "text": "of traditional\nwriting practices.",
    "start": 695.111,
    "duration": 2.168
  },
  {
    "text": "Invention,\ncollaboration, drafting,",
    "start": 697.363,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "revision, and reflection,",
    "start": 699.281,
    "duration": 1.544
  },
  {
    "text": "those all happen\nin the SCP wiki.",
    "start": 700.908,
    "duration": 2.586
  },
  {
    "text": "It embodies storytelling methods",
    "start": 703.577,
    "duration": 1.46
  },
  {
    "text": "with digital media literacy.",
    "start": 705.121,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "Is it a substitute for\na formal writing course?",
    "start": 706.705,
    "duration": 2.378
  },
  {
    "text": "ASU professor, Emily Zarka, PhD,",
    "start": 709.166,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "says no.",
    "start": 711.085,
    "duration": 1.585
  },
  {
    "text": "But it can serve as\na supplemental educational tool,",
    "start": 712.753,
    "duration": 3.128
  },
  {
    "text": "especially for writers\nwho may be hesitant",
    "start": 715.965,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "to jump into creative\nwriting spaces,",
    "start": 718.008,
    "duration": 2.253
  },
  {
    "text": "or for authors looking\nfor a community.",
    "start": 720.344,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "Heck, maybe it has\na place in my syllabus.",
    "start": 722.43,
    "duration": 2.711
  },
  {
    "text": "SCP Foundation is building",
    "start": 725.224,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "and supporting a vibrant\nand creative community",
    "start": 726.851,
    "duration": 2.46
  },
  {
    "text": "that reformulates the\ncrucial human custom",
    "start": 729.395,
    "duration": 2.335
  },
  {
    "text": "of storytelling\nand lore building.",
    "start": 731.814,
    "duration": 1.918
  },
  {
    "text": "And it has the added bonus\nof being creepy AF.",
    "start": 733.816,
    "duration": 3.837
  },
  {
    "text": "An anonymity of reports.",
    "start": 737.736,
    "duration": 1.711
  },
  {
    "text": "Anonymity.",
    "start": 739.53,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "An anonymity of reports.",
    "start": 740.865,
    "duration": 1.418
  },
  {
    "text": "I did it again,",
    "start": 742.366,
    "duration": 0.793
  },
  {
    "text": "anonymity of reports.",
    "start": 743.242,
    "duration": 1.752
  },
  {
    "text": "[bystander chuckles]",
    "start": 745.077,
    "duration": 0.876
  },
  {
    "text": "There's too many Ws in a row.",
    "start": 746.036,
    "duration": 1.502
  }
]